Subject: Re: [T2] convert hydraulic to solid

On Fri, Aug 15, 2003 at 11:14:32AM -0400, Access Systems wrote:
> no you cannot just drop solid lifters in, there are different cam
> followers and they would have to be changed also, and I have been told
> that you have to split the case to put in those kinds of cam followers,
> hyd can just be dropped in.  also VW specs a different cam but I have
> heard many folks use the same cam. 

In a type4 engine the solid lifters can be just dripped in as well.
It's the type1 engine that requires splitting the case to remove the
lifters. But even though many people have moved to hyd from solid and
not changed the cam I still feel it's a bad idea to mix/match metals
that have been work hardened to match.

